            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Beatissimo s<expan><ex>a</ex><abbr>eculo</abbr></expan> <expan><abbr>d<am>d</am></abbr><ex>ominorum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>n<am>n</am></abbr><ex>ostrorum</ex></expan> Valentiniani et V<supplied reason="lost">alentis</supplied> <lb n="2"/>invictiss<supplied reason="lost">i</supplied>morum <expan><abbr>clementissimorumq</abbr><ex>ue</ex></expan> principum <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> polleni <expan><abbr>atqu</abbr><ex>e</ex></expan> praeclara sunt macelli ma<lb break="no" n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">rmora <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>te</supplied>riem longa incuria ac discissione <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="5"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>am non<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="6"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>iam rei <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ublicae</ex></expan> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="7"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>o procons<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> <lb n="8"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>NVSTA<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Die Wendung longa incuria ac discissione spielt vielleicht auf die Unruhen im Zuge des Donatistenstreites an; so gebraucht Augustin, Serm. 46, 15, 39 discissio in Bezug auf die Donatistenspaltung. Reste von roter Farbe in den Buchstaben. Von der Tafel sind 13 Fragmente erhalten. Z.7: [---]o procons[---]: möglicherweise war der Proconsul im Ablativ angegeben.</p>
            </div>
